<plot>In 1958, in a sweltering, converted torpedo factory in Alexandria, Virginia, historian Gerhard L. Weinberg was combing through massive stacks of documents that the U.S. had captured from Nazi Germany-and came across an unknown prize-a secret book dictated by Adolf Hitler in 1928, the unpublished sequel to Mein Kampf.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?241827</url></doc>
